01/08/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament endorsed a decision on Friday (29 July) to deploy Macedonian medical staff to the international peacekeeping mission in Afghanistan. 
The move is part of a trilateral initiative by the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- to send a joint medical team. 
According to Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski, the Macedonian staff will depart for their mission on 8 August. 
(Vecer, Utrinski Vesnik - 30/07/05)
